{# Ventilation advisor — should you open a window? Pure decision math; entity reads (states/now)
   stay in the caller (bedroom_window_advisor, files/automations.yaml). Returns 'stale' (indoor air
   is stale, ventilate), 'cool' (free cooling available), or 'none' (don't suggest). Every non-'none'
   verdict REQUIRES outdoor air to be under the safe cap; the "dirtier than indoors" relative guard
   only applies once outdoor PM is itself ABOVE pm_relative_floor (objectively-safe outdoor air is
   fine to bring in even past a purifier-scrubbed indoor — the purifier re-scrubs it) — so the
   system can never advise ventilating into worse/unsafe air (the smoke guard). Args coerce inside
   (like lighting.jinja) so a caller may pass strings or numbers. Unavailable -> safe 'none'.
   Unit-tested in tests/test_ventilation_macros.py. Tune the comfort band / cool delta / PM cap here.
   'stale' outranks 'cool' when both apply. #}
{%- macro ventilation_advice(indoor_temp, outdoor_temp, indoor_pm, outdoor_pm, air_stale,
                             outdoor_pm10=0, comfort_lo=55, comfort_hi=78, cool_delta=5,
                             pm_safe=25, pm10_safe=50, pm_dirty_margin=10, pm_relative_floor=15) -%}
{%- set it = indoor_temp | float(0) -%}
{%- set ot = outdoor_temp | float(999) -%}
{%- set ip = indoor_pm | float(0) -%}
{%- set op = outdoor_pm | float(999) -%}
{%- set op10 = outdoor_pm10 | float(999) -%}
{%- set stale = air_stale | bool -%}
{# Smoke guard: block on PM2.5 over its cap OR (outdoor PM is itself above pm_relative_floor AND
   MORE THAN pm_dirty_margin µg/m³ dirtier than indoors), AND on coarse PM10 over its own (higher)
   cap. The relative-floor gate is load-bearing: a HEPA purifier drives indoor PM near zero, so the
   bare "dirtier than indoors" term vetoed CO2/cooling ventilation on ANY normal urban outdoor
   reading (e.g. outdoor 12 vs indoor 2). Only veto on relative dirtiness once outdoor is also
   approaching the cap (pm_relative_floor=15); below that the air is good enough to bring in. PM10
   over its own cap still blocks a dust/pollen event that spikes PM10 while PM2.5 stays moderate. #}
{%- if op > pm_safe or (op > pm_relative_floor and op > ip + pm_dirty_margin) or op10 > pm10_safe -%}none
{%- elif stale and comfort_lo <= ot <= comfort_hi -%}stale
{%- elif it > comfort_hi and (it - ot) >= cool_delta -%}cool
{%- else -%}none
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}
